[We checked with Nick Knowles at Pirbright who replied as follows:
"Kuwait had the PanAsia strain in 1996, 1997, and 1998. We had 2
samples in May 1999, but were unable to isolate any virus. Nothing
since then. We have, however, sequenced recent isolates (2001) from
Saudi Arabia, United Arab Emirates, and Bahrain. They are closely
related to each other, but distinct from the UK PanAsia virus (about
8% different at the nucleotide level). They may be related to an
earlier lineage that is part of the PanAsia strain. We are currently
investigating this further. There is no connection with the UK
outbreak."
This article does not give us enough information to know if the
correct strain of vaccine is being used. - Mod.TG
